      "writtenOn": "2020-06-01T20:12:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Is this required by Android or something?  I would just expect an RGBA png with r\u003d0,g\u003d0,b\u003d0?\n\nNo, this was something reed@ added for being able to roundtrip SKPs. With our private meaning, we decode back to kAlpha_8_SkColorType, whereas if we created an RGBA PNG it wouldn\u0027t.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e Can\u0027t webp have an alpha channel too?\n\nYes, but we only need to abuse one format for our SKP round-tripping. I think what you suggest is a reasonable feature, but outside the scope of this CL.",
      "parentUuid": "e9db4b06_16c82414",
